const FACTPACK = `UNCLE MAY'S PRODUCE - FACT BASE (anchor: fix the funnel + product mix). Current as of 2026-06-07.

WHAT IT IS: A build-your-own online grocery for Black-farmed seasonal produce, delivered across south-side Chicago and the south suburbs. Tagline: "Cleaner than Whole Foods. Cheaper than Aldi." Long-term vision is a data + distribution platform for Black food consumption with neighborhood-format physical stores (planned flagship: 10,000 sq ft, Hyde Park, Chicago). THIS review is about the live e-commerce funnel and assortment TODAY, not the store rollout.

THE PROBLEM (the anchor every conclusion must serve):
- Paid conversion ~0.46% vs a 2-4% food-DTC benchmark (measured 2026-05-11; paid ads paused since 2026-05-16 so little fresh paid traffic since).
- Funnel cracks: /shop reach ~25% of sessions, add-to-cart ~5.5%.
- CEO root hypothesis (his words): the narrow produce-only assortment is "an offering Anthony himself wouldn't buy." Fix the offer first, then turn spend back on.

ASSORTMENT (live customer catalog, Airtable base appm6F6H9obydzAM2 / table Catalog):
- 43 active SKUs (47 total). Mix: Greens ~14, Roots ~12, Pantry ~10, Microgreens ~6, Protein ~5.
- Single farm supplier: Run A Way Buckers Club (Pembroke, IL): salad mix, kale, candy carrots, sweet potatoes, potatoes, broccoli, organic dry beans, pea shoots, radishes; proteins (pastured chicken, grass-fed beef short ribs, lamb chops, eggs).
- Genuinely MISSING (real sourcing gap, not a code filter): snacks, heat-and-eat/prepared, broader meats, dry goods/pantry staples, beverages, non-food. Paid shoppers expect a fuller basket.
- A separate Airtable base (app3raEVB9kHeUoHE, 1,025 rows) is a VENDOR SOURCING PIPELINE, not hidden customer inventory. Do not treat it as available SKUs.

PRODUCT-MIX RESET (CEO-approved 2026-05-16, in motion):
- 6 phases: pause paid ads (done) -> audit SKUs -> consumption research (top-30 Black/US x grocery/delivery) -> gap analysis -> sourcing roadmap (Black-owned coverage %, <=250K USD initial inventory) -> expand catalog -> relaunch paid only after at least 1 new category live with 10+ merchandised SKUs plus organic-engagement evidence.
- Locked CEO decisions (2026-05-17): (1) Wave B: sell wholesale commodity staples (bananas, etc.) alongside Black-farmed specialty, each SKU showing a "Black-owned supplier" badge where applicable; (2) demote specialty SKUs (ramps, sunchokes, microgreens, black garlic, daikon) off the hero into a Specialty / What's-in-season rail; (3) Wave E added: Black-owned personal care (soaps, oils, batana hair oil, skin/hair care); (4) no paid Numerator data pull (budget); (5) sourcing owned jointly by Anthony (CEO) + Zoe (COO).
- Black-owned badge is wired in code but inert (no SKU renders one yet).

PRICING & OFFER:
- Build-your-own cart, no fixed boxes, no subscription tier. 20 USD minimum cart (blocks checkout under 20). Typical first cart 30-60 USD (produce + one protein).
- Anchor prices: kale/chard 3.00 (0.3 lb), candy carrots 1.50 (0.5 lb), sweet potato 2.50 each, pea shoots 5.00 (1 oz), beans 6.00-6.65 (1 lb), lamb chops 10.00 (pair), beef short ribs 8.50-12.50 (1 lb), whole chicken ~32, eggs 5.99/dozen.
- NO active promo codes as of 2026-05-18 (FRESH10/FRESH30 retired). Listed price = price paid. Deliberate move to isolate conversion signal without a promo confound. Treat promo codes as a possible future lever, not a current tactic.

DELIVERY & SERVICE AREA:
- Every day, 7 days/week. Customer picks delivery date + window (Morning/Midday/Afternoon/Evening CT) at checkout. No weekly cutoff. Earliest delivery 4 days out; booking horizon 30 days.
- 7.99 USD flat delivery fee inside service area; free pickup at Polsky Center (UChicago, Hyde Park). 100% freshness guarantee (full refund).
- Service area: south-side Chicago + Loop/Near North + Pilsen/Little Village + south suburbs. North-side and far-west ZIPs (Lincoln Park, Lakeview, Austin) are NOT served.
- Operational caveat: customer promise is "every day," but real driver routing still serves whichever subset the team can cover each week (EXP-002 painted-door test running).

CUSTOMER & POSITIONING:
- Target: south-side Chicago / south-suburb households (1-4 people) in the service area who want fresh, ethically sourced produce with no long-term commitment.
- Strategic positioning (do NOT use food-desert framing): affluent / culturally-thriving Black communities with higher willingness to pay; data-driven platform + distribution, not just retail grocery.
- Stated demand signal (survey, 100+ consumers): 97% intent-to-shop, 89.6% would refer. Directional, NOT behavioral proof.

PAID MEDIA (paused):
- Pre-pause spend ~439 USD/wk (~377 Meta across 4 campaigns + ~62 Google Ads). Both paused 2026-05-16. Newsletter, organic social, transactional email continue.

OPERATING CONTEXT:
- Considering hiring an outside CRO/UX OPERATOR (not an auditor) to own the funnel outcome end-to-end. US-based, not Shopify-locked. Shortlist: Barrel, Anatta, Bear Group. Expect 50-120K USD for a 90-day trial. Open question: the platform decision (stay custom Next.js vs go headless Shopify) is coupled to this hire.
- Stack: custom Next.js (Vercel), Stripe embedded checkout (PaymentElement, not hosted redirect), Airtable-driven catalog, Trigger.dev workers, Resend transactional email, Mailchimp newsletter (audience effectively empty), LogRocket+Galileo product analytics (subscription PAUSED ~2 weeks as of 2026-05-28).
- One grandfathered subscription customer (Doina, 55 USD/wk via Stripe direct); no new subscriptions being sold.

CAPITAL (context, NOT the anchor): raising a 400-750K USD SAFE (5M cap, 20% discount) to trigger an SBA 7(a) facility and build the Hyde Park flagship. Investor outreach (Apollo) currently idle (OAuth revoked). Claimed stabilized unit economics: 35% gross margin, 15.3% EBITDA - these are PROJECTIONS/targets, not realized e-commerce results.

PROJECTION vs ACTUAL: Revenue (6.3M Yr1), margins, IRR, and the 82-store rollout are PROJECTIONS. The only behavioral facts are the live funnel metrics (CVR ~0.46%, /shop reach 25%, ATC 5.5%), the 43-SKU catalog, ~439/wk pre-pause spend, and one repeat subscriber. Treat everything else as assumption to be tested.`

const SKILL_SCHEMA = {
  type: 'object',
  additionalProperties: false,
  properties: {
    skill: { type: 'string' },
    headline: { type: 'string', description: 'One-sentence, answer-first conclusion' },
    keyTakeaways: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' }, minItems: 3, maxItems: 7, description: 'Crisp bullets the next phase needs' },
    dataGaps: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' }, description: 'Real data needed to harden this analysis' },
    fullMarkdown: { type: 'string', description: 'The skill Output Format, fully filled in for Uncle Mays' },
  },
  required: ['skill', 'headline', 'keyTakeaways', 'fullMarkdown'],
}

const SYNTH_SCHEMA = {
  type: 'object',
  additionalProperties: false,
  properties: {
    executiveSummary: { type: 'string', description: '3-4 sentence summary' },
    fullMarkdown: { type: 'string', description: 'The complete board-ready strategy review in markdown' },
  },
  required: ['fullMarkdown'],
}

const skillPath = (name) => 'C:\\Users\\Anthony\\.claude\\skills\\' + name + '\\SKILL.md'

function skillPrompt(name, prior) {
  return [
    'You are a McKinsey-caliber strategy consultant running the "' + name + '" analysis skill as one phase of a full strategy engagement for Uncle Mays Produce.',
    '',
    'STEP 1 - Read the skill definition and follow it exactly: read the file at ' + skillPath(name) + ' using the Read tool. Apply its Approach, Workflow, Output Format, and Quality Bar precisely. Your fullMarkdown MUST follow that skill\'s Output Format.',
    '',
    'ANCHORING DECISION (every conclusion must serve this): Fix Uncle Mays funnel and product mix. Get paid conversion from ~0.46% into a healthy food-DTC range, and fix the narrow assortment that paid traffic will not buy.',
    '',
    'FACT BASE:',
    FACTPACK,
    '',
    prior
      ? 'WHAT PRIOR PHASES OF THIS ENGAGEMENT ALREADY CONCLUDED (build on these, reference them, do not repeat their analysis):\n' + prior
      : 'This is the first phase of the engagement. Establish the baseline.',
    '',
    'RULES:',
    '- Answer-first: lead with the conclusion, then support it.',
    '- Use ONLY facts in the fact base or defensible, clearly-labeled assumptions. NEVER invent specific numbers (CVR, CAC, AOV, revenue). If you need a number that is not given, state the assumption and add it to dataGaps.',
    '- Be specific to Uncle Mays (south-side Chicago, Black-farmed produce, 43 SKUs, build-your-own cart, 0.46% paid CVR). No generic strategy boilerplate.',
    '- No em dashes anywhere (house style). Use commas, periods, or colons.',
    '- fullMarkdown = the skill\'s complete Output Format filled in. keyTakeaways = 3-7 bullets the next phase needs. headline = one-sentence conclusion. set skill = "' + name + '".',
  ].join('\n')
}

const PHASES = [
  ['1. Diagnose', ['situation-assessment', 'growth-barriers', 'assumption-audit']],
  ['2. Market Intel', ['market-mapping', 'customer-segmentation', 'competitive-intel', 'profit-pool-analysis']],
  ['3. Strategic Choice', ['strategic-options', 'portfolio-review', 'pricing-strategy', 'business-case-builder']],
  ['4. Operating Model', ['operating-model-design', 'initiative-prioritizer', 'transformation-roadmap']],
  ['5. Risk & Governance', ['risk-and-mitigation', 'war-gaming', 'kpi-architect', 'value-realization']],
  ['6. Communicate', ['narrative-builder', 'stakeholder-alignment', 'decision-memo']],
]

let context = ''
const allSections = []
function fold(results) {
  for (const r of results.filter(Boolean)) {
    context += '\n[' + r.skill + '] ' + r.headline + '\n- ' + r.keyTakeaways.join('\n- ') + '\n'
    allSections.push(r)
  }
}
function runSkill(name, phaseTitle) {
  return agent(skillPrompt(name, context), { label: name, phase: phaseTitle, schema: SKILL_SCHEMA, model: 'sonnet' })
}

